post_text: PTO is seeking 4 officer positions (President, Vice-President, Treasurer, Secretary) for the 2020-2021 year. According to the by-laws these positions must have nominations by the March 19th meeting with positions filled at the April meeting. These elections are conducted each year and the officers are re-elected or new nominations received for the next academic year. Without officers PTO will not exist for the 2020-2021 academic year. If you are interested in running for office please respond to this post as soon as possible.

post_text:
Parents/Guardians of Felicity-Franklin Local Schools,
The 2014-2015 Kroger Community Rewards Program begins May 1, 2014 and enrollment officially opened April 1, 2014. All supporters must re-enroll online to continue supporting your organization.

Re-enrolling only takes a few moments and is completed in a few simple steps.

To re-enroll:

1. Visit our website at www.krogercommunityrewards.com.

2. Sign in using your email address and password. If you have forgotten your password, just click on "forgot password" and a link will be sent to your email to change your password.

3. Enter your organization's five digit NPO number or the first three letters of the organization's name, click search.

4. Select your organization by clicking on the circle to the left of your organization's name.

5. Save changes.

post_text:
Dear Friends and Parents,
I am sure that many of you have heard of the tragic passing of one of our students, third grader, Adrian Akers. While our thoughts and prayers are with family, the Felicity Franklin PTO has set up a fund to help pay for the funeral expenses for Adrian. We are looking for $3000 to help cover the funeral costs. The fund has been set up at RiverHills Bank in Felicity. Any amount donated would be appreciated. Thank you. Please share this post to your own Facebook page.

Dear Friends and Parents,
I am sure that many of you have heard of the tragic passing of one of our students, third grader, Adrian Akers. While our thoughts and prayers are with family, the Felicity Franklin PTO has set up a fund to help pay for the funeral expenses for Adrian. We are looking for $3000 to help cover the funeral costs. The fund has been set up at RiverHills Bank in Felicity. Any amount donated would be appreciated. Thank you. Please share this post to your own Facebook page.
